    "course_title": "FUNDAMENTAL PRINCIPLES OF VETERINARY ANATOMY",
    "description": "A detailed consideration of gross anatomical structure with emphasis on major anatomical patterns present in species important to veterinary medicine. The dog is used as a model domestic mammal and comparisons with other species are considered. All body systems are dissected. Clinical implications of these dissections are emphasized.",
